title._content: A westbound Southwest Limited passing through the San Felipe Idian Reservation at Algodones, New Mexico, June 1974

description._content: Original Caption: A westbound Southwest Limited passing through the San Felipe Idian Reservation at Algodones, New Mexico, near Albuquerque. This Amtrak train runs between Los Angeles California, and Chicago. Most U.S. intercity passenger trains are the responsibility of the corporation which is trying to improve rail service, June 1974 U.S. National Archives’ Local Identifier: 412-DA-13540 Photographer: O'Rear, Charles, 1941- Subjects: Algodones (New Mexico) Environmental Protection Agency Project DOCUMERICA Persistent URL: research.archives.gov/description/555992 Repository: Still Picture Records Section, Special Media Archives Services Division (NWCS-S), National Archives at College Park, 8601 Adelphi Road, College Park, MD, 20740-6001.
